  id: Patella_L
  partName: Patella Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left patella is a small but important bone positioned within the quadriceps
    tendon at the front of the canine stifle joint. It enhances the mechanical advantage
    of the quadriceps muscle by improving force transmission during extension of
    the hindlimb. The patella also stabilizes the tendon and protects the stifle
    joint from excessive stress during movement.
  - Proper positioning and alignment are essential for smooth joint function, efficient
    locomotion, and balanced weight-bearing activities. The bone contributes significantly
    to running, jumping, and coordinated hindlimb motion.
